ISKCON, the official website of the International Society for Krishna Consciousness (ISKCON) The Society for Krishna Consciousness (ISKCON), often simply known as "the Hare Krishnas", is a Gaudiya Vaishnava Hindu religious organisation. ISKCON was founded in 1966 in New York City by A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swami Prabhupada. ISKCON today is a worldwide confederation of more than 550 centers, temples, and projects. Its core beliefs are based on select traditional Hindu scriptures, principally the Bhagavad Gita, the Srimad Bhagavatam, and the Bhagavata Purana
